This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of regularization techniques and cost-sensitive learning, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also deals with information retrieval systems, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
